	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1016 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.46]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Check the discussion boards at www.EQDiva.COM . That should provide all the answers you need on this topic. <br><br>Based on what I have read there: Yes, FT items work for bards (which is nice since Meditation skill caps a 1). Yes, mana bonus items do increase the bard's mana pool.&nbsp;&nbsp;Yes, bard mana is INT based.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
