	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=103877019543646>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103877019543646>Soloing Reds in Stonebrunt lvl 30+</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103877019543646#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Dec 1st 2:39 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=139081><span id= >Meaelstorm</span></a><br><span id=notbold>42 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.23]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well bards are just something else. For the past few sessions of EQ i have been perfecting a method of soloing in Stonebrunt (one of the best underused zones for lvl 25-45). I have come to this method: 1) Find the best, least crowded with obsticles, and away from mob traffic areas. 2)Use your percussion instrument at all times. 3) Single pull whatever you wish with Selo's Consonant Chain, preferably even to red cons, and bring 'em to your area (this is all very redundant but still worth saying). 4) Start twisting Amplification, Fufil's Curtailing Chant&nbsp;&nbsp;Brosco's Boastful Bellow and Selo's Consonant Chain while running around in circles (you can modify this to replace BBB with DDD). 5) The order goes: Selo's, Fufil's, Amp, Selo's, BBB, Fufil's, Selo's, BBB, Fufil's, then repeat. I added amplification after i saw how it improves singing songs drastically, and it did so with BBB improving it from 16dd (lvl 30) to 24dd. Also the percussion instruments helps a lot in this case since Fufil's is percussion and it will give the DoT a bonus to dmg. This is an easy little way of killing tough red mobs that would easily crush you. Theres not that much loot but its great for the tailors since you will be killing a lot of things that drop pelts. Feel free to try it.</p>&nbsp;<br>Heldor Menhir<br>Mystic<br>Zalizz Meaelstorm<br>Master<br>Silderan<br>Bard Extraordinaire<br>E'ci Server</td></td></tr>
