	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=195180><span id= >Wara</span></a><br><span id=notbold>7 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Just wanted to add that you might want to keep in mind about the stats/ aggro discussion that bard tactics change with the lvl.<br><br>E.g. once you get your mana charm song you would even love to have more int to keep going on and on.<br><br>And don't emphazise str too much (remember you are bard anyways). Later on you are not tanking anymore (why? just take a look what you can do with your buffs and playing an instrument). Just keep some to carry that loot.<br><br>Aggro is a big problem if you are fighting in a group. Even if you think you are almost as good as a tank in the early lvls, just stay back for the first (couple of) combat rounds playing some buffs. It's a bit tricky to get the timing when to engage yourself.<br>Hey, but what fun would be left if the talent of a bard could be jugded by her stats?</p>&nbsp;<br>Wara Fairytune - Woodelf Bardess from Kelethin/Sol Ro<br>56 songs available at your local dealer - AAlready 6 remixes as well!<br>New Horizon</td></td></tr>
