	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=56573><span id= >Valdon</span></a><br><span id=notbold>482 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.64]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Anyone that has seem my posts know I have pretty much every char combo possible. I also have a bard. Im not AS familiar with them, I know that the rules for a bard are TOTALLY different. I do know one thing for sure, every class gets basically the same spells over and over, so ANY tactic that works can almost always be applied on a lower level. Like I was told I cant duel kite or quad kite with a 14 druid. They were wrong. I was able to root untill I was ready, snare both... pull them in close and then cast cascade of hail and run around them in a circle. I was told it was impossible.<br><br>All I am saying is you DO get DD pretty early, and you do get speed early on. So the level is different, but the lesson is the same. Bards do seem to have a more broad span between getting that next spell that does the same thing - because they get a spell a level. But it IS the same thing.<br><br>So have fun, be careful. and dont be so literal. take the lession, improvise a bit... etc. play the game, dont just play a cardboard cutout of everyone elses tactics. <br><br>Hell with my chanter sometimes i reverse fear kite. *IM* the one thats scared. I agro the mob, he chases me and my pet hits it in the back. it works sometimes... so dont let anyone tell you you can or CANT do something game, try it for yourself. Thats the difference between knowledge and being a mindless drone.<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>· 'Valdon Gravedancer' Terris-Thule. Dwarven Cleric 32nd season.<br>· 'Junglebug Sugarpants' Terris-Thule. Halfling Druid. 39th season.<br>· 'Shinook Eldergod' Terris-Thule. Troll Shaman of 32nd season</td></td></tr>
