	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=103427236294208>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103427236294208>RE: Best class</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103427236294208#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Oct 10th 2:10 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1016 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Now I don't understand your question. Speed for what? Running speed then nothing is faster than a bard. But druids and wizards can teleport from zone to zone.&nbsp;&nbsp;Druids are the travel masters. Fighting?  For damage output rogues are the best.  For taking damage warriors are the best.  Monks, Paladins and Shadowknights fall somewhere between.  Do you want to solo mostly? Then druid, necromancer or bard are your best bet with monks and rangers coming in pretty close.<br><br>Do you want to 'mix it up' and be in the thick of things or would you rather stand off at a safe distance and let someone else do the work? Are you the kind of person who needs to be in the front of the action? Or are you happy being a supporting character while others do 'the dirty work'?<br><br>I think your best bet is to play each class to level 20 and get a feel for it. Then settle on the one you like the best - the one that fits your style.  I like rogues and bards. They fit my style.  They may not fit yours.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
