	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=74761><span id= >Balnore</span></a><br><span id=notbold>99 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.98]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hehe, without really knowing it, I have found I have done pretty much what Slipskin has suggested.&nbsp;&nbsp;I played a paladin to 30 (broke) and hated it, no offense to my pally friends.  Then I played a shaman, thinking I was making a necro, and got very bored by 15.  Then I started a necro and had fun til 36, when I got bored with it and not finding groups at all.  So I made a druid which I love to this day, but have slowed down playing at 54, because I desparately wanted to melee again.  Tried a warrior and a monk, leveling them to 27 and 24 respectively and found that the monk was much more interesting to play.  It seems I like a challenge.  <br><br>So I go all out and start a bard and have found my calling after leveling him to 38 and counting. Sure your fingers get tired and you can't type and twist, and lag in Luclin makes it impossible to learn to swarmkite there, but it is SOOOO much fun to be able to switch from fear-kiting, to charm-kiting, to chant-kiting, to grouping support, or grouping toe-to-toe.  I love being a jack of all trades and find my first groupchat is Hi, what can I do for this group today?  Confuses newbies, but experienced players help me find my place.  BARDS ROCK!<br><br>Glad I found the class.</p>&nbsp;<br>Davidon<br>Wood Elf Druid<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547810" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547810</a><br><br>Sinfonian<br>Half-Elf Bard<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547835" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547835</a></td></td></tr>
